episodes.description:
We left the Jehovah’s Witness organization—not because we stopped loving God, but because we started loving Him more. The deeper we studied Scripture and sought truth, the more we realized the organization was teaching the commandments of men as doctrine (Matthew 15:9).

But our journey isn’t about bitterness—it’s about freedom, truth, and love. We’re still preaching—to those inside and those who’ve left—because we believe Jesus sets people free, not religion.

